## 08 â€” Implementation Path  

### Phase 1 â€” Mapping & Internal Recognition  

- Build and regularly update a **Multi-Lever Support Map** across four domains.  
- Introduce support-point concepts in policy debates, education, and media.  

### Phase 2 â€” Narrative & Policy Fixation  

- Align national security, industrial, and foreign policy documents with SP-OS framing.  
- Standardize language around â€œsupport lever,â€ â€œsystem node,â€ â€œstructural pillar.â€  

### Phase 3 â€” External Embedding  

- Promote joint investments and co-located R&D with key partners.  
- Secure island roles in:  
  - Supply-chain security agreements,  
  - Technology alliances,  
  - Standards bodies.  
- Work with financial and insurance actors to internalize island risk into systemic models.  

### Phase 4 â€” Resonance & Immunity Build-Up  

- Measure and strengthen cross-binding intensity with top partner sets.  
- Integrate **StrategicLiteracyOS** and **CivImmunity modules** into education and communication.  

### Phase 5 â€” Scenario Management & Adaptive Governance  

- Run regular SP-OS-informed scenario exercises (continuation / fixation / marginalization).  
- Adjust lever development and embedding strategies based on global and domestic trends.  

